{% comment %}
  Section: gazelle-strip.liquid
  Display name: "Gazelle Strip"

  Single full-width image band (e.g. the Montagud publisher strip).

  16 July changes:

  1. NATIVE COLOUR SCHEME (`color_scheme` → `color-{{ scheme }}` class).
     ⚠️ STRUCTURE CHANGED to make this work: .gazelle-strip was the max-width:1200px
     element, so a background on it would only paint the centre column, not the full
     band. Split into an outer full-bleed .gazelle-strip (carries the scheme class
     and the background) and an inner .gazelle-strip__inner (max-width 1200px +
     gutter). Same split as gazelle-focus and gazelle-hero.
     Verified against the repo: Horizon 3.4 exposes --color-background,
     --color-foreground and --color-border in assets/base.css. currentColor is used
     in preference where possible — it needs no variable name at all.

  2. ⚠️ MOBILE IMAGE FALLBACK — this was a live bug, the same one gazelle-hero and
     gazelle-focus both had. `.desktop-image { display: none }` fired on mobile
     unconditionally, while `mobile_image` is labelled optional. So the strip went
     BLANK on phones whenever no mobile image was set. Now keyed to a `has-mobile`
     class on the wrapper, so it falls back to the desktop image (scaled).

  3. Padding is now a setting (was a hardcoded 20px) — it matters once the band has
     a colour of its own.

  4. width/height on <img> — stops layout shift and clears the theme-check offence.

  5. Placeholder tinted from the scheme rather than a fixed #f0f0f0 grey, which
     would have looked wrong on Scheme 5 Charcoal.

  NOT ADDED (deliberate — not requested): a link setting. gazelle-hero and
  gazelle-focus both take an optional `url` per block; this strip has no way to be
  clickable. For a publisher banner that's probably wanted, but it's a scope call,
  not a bug. Say the word and it's a three-line change.
{% endcomment %}

<div
  class="gazelle-strip color-{{ section.settings.color_scheme }}"
  id="gazelle-strip-{{ section.id }}"
>
  <div class="gazelle-strip__inner{% if section.settings.mobile_image != blank %} has-mobile{% endif %}">

    {% if section.settings.desktop_image != blank %}
      <img
        class="desktop-image"
        src="{{ section.settings.desktop_image | image_url: width: 1200 }}"
        alt="{{ section.settings.desktop_image.alt | escape }}"
        width="{{ section.settings.desktop_image.width }}"
        height="{{ section.settings.desktop_image.height }}"
        loading="lazy"
      >
    {% else %}
      <div class="gazelle-strip__placeholder">
        <span>Add a desktop image in the theme editor</span>
      </div>
    {% endif %}

    {% if section.settings.mobile_image != blank %}
      <img
        class="mobile-image"
        src="{{ section.settings.mobile_image | image_url: width: 600 }}"
        alt="{{ section.settings.mobile_image.alt | escape }}"
        width="{{ section.settings.mobile_image.width }}"
        height="{{ section.settings.mobile_image.height }}"
        loading="lazy"
      >
    {% endif %}

  </div>
</div>

{% style %}
  /* Outer band: full-bleed so the colour scheme paints edge to edge. */
  #gazelle-strip-{{ section.id }} {
    padding: {{ section.settings.padding_top }}px 0 {{ section.settings.padding_bottom }}px;
  }

  #gazelle-strip-{{ section.id }} .gazelle-strip__inner {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 20px;
  }

  #gazelle-strip-{{ section.id }} img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
  }

  #gazelle-strip-{{ section.id }} .mobile-image {
    display: none;
  }

  /* Tinted from the scheme rather than a fixed grey. */
  #gazelle-strip-{{ section.id }} .gazelle-strip__placeholder {
    height: 120px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 8%, transparent);
    color: color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 55%, transparent);
  }

  @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {
    /* Only swap to the mobile image when one actually EXISTS.
       Without the .has-mobile guard the desktop image was hidden unconditionally,
       so a strip with no mobile image rendered blank. */
    #gazelle-strip-{{ section.id }} .gazelle-strip__inner.has-mobile .desktop-image {
      display: none;
    }
    #gazelle-strip-{{ section.id }} .gazelle-strip__inner.has-mobile .mobile-image {
      display: block;
    }
  }
{% endstyle %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Gazelle Strip",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "gazelle-strip-section",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "desktop_image",
      "label": "Desktop image"
    },
    {
      "type": "image_picker",
      "id": "mobile_image",
      "label": "Mobile image (optional)",
      "info": "If empty, the desktop image is used on mobile."
    },
    {
      "type": "color_scheme",
      "id": "color_scheme",
      "label": "Colour scheme",
      "default": "scheme-1",
      "info": "Sets the band background behind and around the image."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Spacing"
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_top",
      "label": "Top padding",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 100,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 20
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "padding_bottom",
      "label": "Bottom padding",
      "min": 0,
      "max": 100,
      "step": 4,
      "unit": "px",
      "default": 20
    }
  ],
  "presets": [
    {
      "name": "Gazelle Strip"
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
